sidebar-post-title">Advanced CSS positioning using the position property</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/css-display-property/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">5</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">CSS display types</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post active"><a href="/css-advanced-background-images/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">6</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">Advanced background image manipulation using CSS</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/css-units/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">7</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">CSS units ‚Äî there are more than you think... ü§î</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/css-flexboxes/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">8</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">The comprehensive guide to CSS flexboxes</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/fullscreen-image-hero/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">9</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">How to create a full-page hero image (HTML & CSS)</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/style-a-navigation-bar-css/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">10</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">Styling a navigation bar using CSS</span></a></li> <li class="sidebar-post "><a href="/css-text-properties-and-google-fonts/"><span class="sidebar-post-number">11</span> <span class="sidebar-post-title">CSS text properties, and how to use Google Fonts on your website</span></a></li> </ol> </aside> </aside> <div class="post-content"> <article class="markdown-body" itemprop="articleBody"> <p>Background images can do more than you think - learn about cool ways to manipulate background images using CSS‚Ä¶</p> <h2 id="getting-started">Getting started</h2> <p>I think that it is best to learn by doing, so I highly recommend following along in all my tutorials. To follow along start by making a new project folder with <code>index.html</code> and <code>style.css</code> files in it. Add the following code to your <code>index.html</code>:</p><pre class="language-HTML highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-HTML"><span class="token doctype">&lt;!DOCTYPE html></span>
<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>html</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
    <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>head</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
        <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>title</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>CSS advanced background images DEMO<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>title</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
        <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>link</span> <span class="token attr-name">rel</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>stylesheet<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span> <span class="token attr-name">href</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>style.css<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
    <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
    <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>body</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
        <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>Background images<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
    <span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>
</code></pre><p>The image that I will be using for the demos in this article is the following:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg" alt="An image of mountains" width="1500" height="1000" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>And add a <code>background-image</code> to the <code>body</code> element in your <code>style.css</code> file:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>If you don‚Äôt know how to use the <code>background-image</code> property, <a href="/basic-css-properties/#the-background-image-property">check here first</a> - I‚Äôll be here when you get back!</p> <p>The reason for the <code>body</code> height is so that we can scroll on our page - you will see why this is relevant later in the tutorial. <code>150vh</code> basically means <a href="/newsletter/">150% of the viewport height</a>.</p> <p>When you open your HTML file in a browser, it should look like this:</p> <p><picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png" alt="Text on top of the mountains background image" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>If yours is looking right, let‚Äôs continue!</p> <h2 id="background-image-related-properties">Background-image related properties</h2> <p>As well as the <code>background-image</code> property, there are many properties that modify how the <code>background-image</code> is <em>displayed</em>:</p> <ul> <li><code>background-size</code></li> <li><code>background-position</code></li> <li><code>background-repeat</code></li> <li><code>background-size</code></li> </ul> <p>In this article, I‚Äôll be going through each one individually‚Ä¶ Let‚Äôs get started!</p> <h2 id="background-size">background-size</h2> <p>Remember our original image?<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/cover.jpg" alt="An image of mountains" width="1500" height="1000" loading='lazy'> </picture><br /> However on our page, it is super-zoomed in on the sky!<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/base-code.png" alt="Text on top of the mountains background image" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture><br /> This is because, by default, the <code>background-image</code> is set to the actual dimensions of the image (<code>4272px</code> by <code>2848px</code>)</p> <p>Let‚Äôs fix this up!</p> <p>The <code>background-size</code> property can be set to either <code>cover</code>, <code>contain</code> or any unit value (eg. <code>1500px</code>).</p> <p><code>background-size: cover</code> sets the image size so that it covers the entire element (in this case the <code>body</code>).</p> <p><code>background-size: contain</code> makes sure that all of the <code>background-image</code> is shown within the element.</p> <p>In this case, we‚Äôll want to use <code>cover</code> - this way we can see most of the image, but it will cover the whole screen! Let‚Äôs try it out:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> cover<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-cover.png" alt="Most of the image is now shown!" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture><br /> If you scroll down, you can see more of the image - this is because it is covering the <code>body</code> element (which is 150% of the viewport height), not the actual screen.</p> <p>You can also set the <code>background-size</code> to an actual value - change your CSS to this:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 2000px<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Change this line from cover */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-size-2000px.png" alt="The image width is 2000px" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture><br /> Again if you scroll down, you will see a bit more of the image.</p> <h2 id="background-attachment-fixed">background-attachment: fixed</h2> <p><code>background-attachment: fixed;</code> is used to to make the image stay in the same place as you scroll down. It is kind of like <a href="/css-position-property/#position-fixed"><code>position: fixed</code></a> but for background images. Let‚Äôs try it out and see what it does:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 2000px<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-attachment</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> fixed<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Now when you scroll down the page, the <code>background-image</code> will not move with it:<br /> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/bg-attachment-fixed.gif" alt="When you scroll down the page, the `background-image` does not move with it" width="1364" height="618" loading='lazy'></p> <blockquote> <p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong><br /> Before continuing, remove the <code>background-attachment: fixed</code> line, so that we can focus on the other properties. Your CSS should look like this:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 2000px<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
  </code></pre></blockquote> <h2 id="background-position">background-position</h2> <p>As you can see, not the whole image is shown - but which part <em>is</em> shown?<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/default-position-highlight.jpg" alt="The top-left corner of the image is shown" width="1500" height="1000" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>What if we want to show the center of the image?<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/center-center-highlight.jpg" alt="The center of the image" width="1500" height="1000" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>This is where we can use the <code>background-position</code> property:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 2000px<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-x</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-y</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/position-center-center.png" alt="The website using position: center center" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>The <code>background-position-x</code> and <code>background-position-y</code> are used to position the image horizontally (<code>x</code>) and vertically (<code>y</code>).</p> <p>The accepted values for <code>background-position-x</code> are:</p> <ul> <li><code>left</code></li> <li><code>center</code></li> <li><code>right</code></li> </ul> <p>And for <code>background-position-y</code>:</p> <ul> <li><code>top</code></li> <li><code>center</code></li> <li><code>bottom</code></li> </ul> <p>In addition, both accept numerical values eg <code>200px</code>. They are calculated from the top-right corner. So for example, a <code>background-position-x</code> of <code>500px</code> would be <code>500px</code> from the left, and a <code>background-position-y</code> of <code>300px</code> would be <code>300px</code> from the top.</p> <p>For the moment, let‚Äôs leave both as <code>center</code>‚Ä¶ (although you can play around if you want üòâ)</p> <h2 id="background-repeat">background-repeat</h2> <p>You know those tiled backgrounds? Often this looks ugly but can work well with repeating textures. In this case, we‚Äôre just going to use our mountain image so that the tiling is more obvious. Let‚Äôs see what happens when we tile an image:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 500px<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Change this line from 2000px, so that we can see it tiling */</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-x</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-y</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/tiled.png" alt="The mountains image is now tiled!" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <p>Wait, what? But this is a rip-off! We didn‚Äôt even use <code>background-repeat</code>!</p> <p>This is because a background has <code>background-repeat</code> turned on by default. The only reason that it didn‚Äôt happen before was that our image was so large that it didn‚Äôt need tiling.</p> <p>The <code>background-repeat</code> property has two main values: <code>repeat</code> and <code>no-repeat</code>. It‚Äôs as simple as that!</p> <p>By default <code>background-repeat</code> is set to <code>repeat</code>, so you will not usually need to use that. However, what if you want to turn off the tiling? Let‚Äôs try it out:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 500px<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-x</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-y</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-repeat</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> no-repeat<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/no-repeat.png" alt="The image is no longer tiled" class="screenshot-white" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture><br /> (the reason that the image is near the bottom of the screen is because the body height is 150%, remember?)</p> <p>There we go! That‚Äôs how the <code>background-repeat</code> property works in CSS!</p> <h2 id="multiple-backgrounds">Multiple backgrounds</h2> <p>You will notice that now there is ugly white around our image. What if we wanted to make that, let‚Äôs say, orange for example? Believe it or not, you can actually specify multiple backgrounds in CSS!</p> <p>The first background will be put on the screen, and other backgrounds after will be layered on top.</p> <p>So, let‚Äôs try it out! Remember, the <code>background-color: orange</code> comes first because we want it <em>below</em> the image:</p><pre class="language-CSS highlighter-MySyntaxHighlighter"><code class="language-CSS"><span class="token selector">body</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
    <span class="token property">height</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 150vh<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-color</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> orange<span class="token punctuation">;</span>  <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
    <span class="token property">background-image</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token url">url('https://codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/mountains.jpg')</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-size</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> 500px<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-x</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-position-y</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> center<span class="token punctuation">;</span>
    <span class="token property">background-repeat</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> no-repeat<span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/* Add this line */</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span>
</code></pre><p>Result:<br /> <picture> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=webp&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=webp&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=webp&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=webp&w=2880 4x' type='image/webp'> <source srcset='https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=png&w=720, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=png&w=1440 2x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=png&w=2160 3x, https://cdn.statically.io/img/codetheweb.blog/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png?f=png&w=2880 4x' type='image/png'> <img src="/assets/img/posts/css-advanced-background-images/color-and-img.png" alt="Now the white background has been replaced with orange" width="1366" height="768" loading='lazy'> </picture></p> <h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2> <p>Okay, there we go! You‚Äôve just learned a bunch of cool stuff that you can do with background images, and these properties come in handy very often. If you have any feedback or need any help, <a href="#disqus_thread">hit me up in the comments</a>.</p> <p>Also if you liked this article, I‚Äôd love it if you <a href="#share">shared it</a> or signed up <a href="/newsletter/">to the newsletter</a>. It takes a lot of time and effort to make a blog (25,000 words and counting), and I‚Äôd really appreciate if you did one (or both!) of those things.</p> <p>Have fun and I‚Äôll see you next time, where I‚Äôll be talking about <a href="/css-units/">the different types of units in CSS</a> and what they do - there are more than you think!</p> </article> <section class="after-post"> <a href="https://www.buymeacoffee.com/CodeTheWeb" class="btn sidebar-btn donate-btn"><span class="emoji"><span>‚ù§Ô∏è</span><div class="animation-bg"></div></span><span> Support me?</span></a> <div class="in-post-stream newsletter card-style"> <div class="explainer">Get a weekly email filled with resources to learn web development <a href="/newsletter/" style="font-weight: normal">(more info)</a></div> <form accept-charset="UTF-8" action="https://usebasin.com/f/01ede12f14de" method="POST" oninput="input(this)" onblur="blurred(this)" class="newsletter-form"> <label for="newsletter-form-email">Enter your email address (required)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-email" name="email" type="email" placeholder="Enter your email address" class="card-style" required> <input type="submit" value="Here we go..." class="card-style"> <div class="extra"> <div class="measurer"> <label for="newsletter-form-found-out">How did you find out about Code The Web? (required)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-found-out" name="found-out" type="text" placeholder="How did you find out about Code The Web?" class="card-style" required> <div class="row"> <label for="newsletter-form-fname">First name (optional)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-fname" name="fname" type="text" placeholder="(First name)" class="card-style"> <label for="newsletter-form-lname">Last name (optional)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-lname" name="lname" type="text" placeholder="(Last name)" class="card-style"> <label for="newsletter-form-url">Your URL (optional)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-url" name="url" type="text" placeholder="(Your URL)" class="card-style"> </div> <label for="newsletter-form-extra-comments">Anything else you want to tell me? (optional)</label> <input id="newsletter-form-extra-comments" name="extra-comments" type="text" placeholder="(Anythi